page.title: 05Cobham Park
page.content: Cobham Park is a rather hilly area, uncultivated and quite thickly wooded, with a variety of deciduous trees, principally birch and oak. The park, roughly divided into a number of "woods", includes a deer park, though few deer can now be seen. The many footpaths provide interesting nature walks. Cobham Hall lies at the heart of this extensive estate. It is an old manor house with a long history and is the principal site of interest in the area. It is now a girls' private school. The park also contains a mausoleum and the site of a Roman villa.
